<H3> <TI>   Talks Deadlocked Over Deputies Issue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Talks Deadlocked Over Deputies Issue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB0706203594 Luanda Radio Nacional Network in Portuguese 
1900 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0706203594 </F>
<F P=104>  Luanda Radio Nacional Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report from Lusaka by correspondent Alves Antonio] </F>
  [Text] Good evening. The question of the swearing in of 
UNITA [National Union for the Total Independence of Angola] 
members of Parliament is still on the negotiating table, 
although it has been under discussing for five days now. The 
UNITA representative is still evasive, thus hindering the 
debate. Today's morning and afternoon sessions lasted eight 
hours, but as a whole it was a totally unproductive day. 
Tomorrow, government and UNITA negotiators will return to the 
Mulungushi Conference Center to try to find a solution. 

</TEXT>

