<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Government-UNITA Clashes 9-10 Jun </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Roundup of Government-UNITA Clashes 9-10 Jun </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Luanda Maintains Control in Kuito </H4>

<F P=102> MB0906150994 Luanda Radio Nacional Network in Portuguese 
1200 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0906150994 </F>
<F P=104>  Luanda Radio Nacional Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report from Kuito by correspondent Abel Abraao] </F>
  [Text] War continues in Kuito, Bie Province. Fifteen days 
have passed since clashes erupted, killing more people. Over 
the past days, government troops have made many prisoners among 
Jonas Savimbi's men and captured a quantity of war materiel. 
Our correspondent Abel Abraao has further details. 
  [Begin recording] [Abraao] The atmosphere is still 
characterized by war here in Kuito. The Black Cockerel's men 
continue to attack the martyred city of Kuito. After 15 days of 
fierce clashes and heavy shellings, government forces killed 
[words indistinct] Jonas Savimbi's men and captured 42 AKM's, 
six [words indistinct], three RPG-7's, one M-79's, [words 
indistinct], 15 hand grenades, a quantity of rounds of 
ammunition, 25 clips, (?two) missiles, and two machineguns. 
Government forces also destroyed one vehicle. Brigadier 
Simeone Mukume, second commander of the FAA Operational Command 
in Bie, told our reporter that the political and military 
situation is worrying in the city of Kuito at the present moment. 
  [Mukume] The situation is worrying because forces belonging 
to the National Union for the Total Independence of Angola 
[UNITA] continue to move men from the neighboring Province of 
Huambo, as well as war materiel from Cuando Cubango. 
  [Abraao] At this moment, the situation is worrying, but it 
is under the control of government forces. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

