<H4>    UNITA Shells Kuito </H4>

<F P=102> MB0906210094 Luanda TPA Television Network in Portuguese 
1930 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0906210094 </F>
<F P=104>  Luanda TPA Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] War continues in the city of Kuito in Bie Province. 
The National Union for the Total Independence of Angola [UNITA] 
has resumed shelling the city, hitting defenseless people. Our 
correspondent Abel Abraao has further details. 
  [Begin Abraao recording] UNITA resumed shelling the city of 
Kuito yesterday afternoon, after a break in the morning. The 
shelling has continued until now, wounding nine civilians -- 
four in Cunje commune -- and killing five others. Despite the 
apparent reduction in actions by the Black Cockerel's troops 
over the past 24 hours, the military situation in Kuito has not 
changed in any way. It is believed that this atmosphere is due 
to the losses suffered by UNITA troops over the past 15 days. 
This is the assessment made by Simeone Mukume, second commander 
of the operational command of the government forces in Bie. 
Brig. Mukume said silencing guns only depends on UNITA. When 
the Armed Forces for the Liberation of Angola halts their 
attacks, the war will end. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

