<H3> <TI>   University Closed `Indefinitely' After Demonstration </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    University Closed `Indefinitely' After Demonstration </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB0906182494 Kaduna Radio Nigeria in English 1700 GMT 9 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> AB0906182494 </F>
<F P=104>  Kaduna Radio Nigeria </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The University of Illorin has been closed 
indefinitely. This followed a peaceful demonstration by students 
of the institution, demanding for the improvement of basic 
amenities on the campus. A statement by the university 
authorities today directed the students to vacate their campuses 
by 4 o'clock in the afternoon [1500 GMT]. Our correspondent, 
who visited the campuses, reports that the students have started 
moving with their property out of their hostels, in compliance 
to the order, while policemen have been drafted to ensure the 
safety of life and property. 

</TEXT>

