<F P=101> Nigeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Lagos Threatens To `Deal Ruthlessly' With Agitators </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Lagos Threatens To `Deal Ruthlessly' With Agitators </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB0906182994 Kaduna Radio Nigeria in English 1700 GMT 9 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> AB0906182994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kaduna Radio Nigeria </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Federal Government has warned that it would not 
condone any overtly political remarks from any group or 
individual in the country. The chief of general staff, 
Lieutenant General Oladipo Diya, stated this in Lagos. Gen. 
Diya maintained that the law would deal ruthlessly with persons 
agitating for open rebellion against the government. He 
therefore asked pressure groups and agitators for the 
installation of any person they conceive as the winner of the 
June 12 election to refrain from such acts, in the interest of 
the nation. The chief of general staff reminded such political 
activists and social critics that the annulled June 12 election 
was now history. 

</TEXT>

