<F P=100> WEST AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Nigeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rulers of Eastern States Pledge Loyalty to Lagos </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rulers of Eastern States Pledge Loyalty to Lagos </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB0906222094 Lagos NTA Television Network in English 2000 
GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB0906222094 </F>
<F P=104>  Lagos NTA Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The traditional rulers of the seven eastern states 
have pledged their loyalty to the Federal Government. In a 
statement signed by the chairman of Imo state council of indieze 
[traditional rulers], Eze Onu Egoke, on behalf of the 
traditional rulers of the seven eastern states, they said they 
did not want secession, but a united Nigeria. The statement 
also said the traditional rulers had accepted to attend the 
constitutional conference which, they say, offers Nigerians the 
opportunity to air their views effectively on issues that affect 
them. They said they believed in democracy and the return of 
Nigeria to democratic rule as early as possible. The statement 
was issued following the meeting the traditional rulers had with 
the chief of general staff on the current political situation in 
the country. 

</TEXT>

