<F P=100> CENTRAL AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Burundi </F>
<H3> <TI>   Soldiers Attacked in Bujumbura Cafe; 4 Dead </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Soldiers Attacked in Bujumbura Cafe; 4 Dead </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA1206194594 Dar es Salaam Radio Tanzania External Service 
in English 1600 GMT 12 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1206194594 </F>
<F P=104>  Dar es Salaam Radio Tanzania External Service 
in English 1600 GMT 12 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Armed villagers attacked soldiers near Burundi's 
capital, Bujumbura, and four people were killed when a grenade 
was thrown into a crowded cafe in the city. Reports said men 
armed with automatic weapons attacked the Army post in Kaidi at 
Nyambuye, 20 km from Bujumbura. Diplomats said the attackers 
had not been identified and the motives were unclear. The 
government had recently been conducting searches for illegal 
weapons, apparently fearing attacks on government forces. They 
had no information of casualties in the attack and official 
sources in Bujumbura declined to comment. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

