<F P=100> EAST AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Djibouti </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government, FRUD Reportedly Agree To End Fighting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government, FRUD Reportedly Agree To End Fighting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1206201694 Paris Radio France International in French 1830 
GMT 12 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1206201694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio France International </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In Djibouti, official sources report that the 
government and the FRUD [Front for Restoration of Unity and 
Democracy] have agreed to end the fighting. That being said, 
negotiations for the FRUD were led by Ougoureh Kifle, whose 
legitimacy as secretary general of the movement is strongly 
disputed by many, and particularly by Ahmed Dini, the FRUD 
leader. 

</TEXT>

