  [Excerpt] Shooting has been going on since Thursday [9 
June] in the Commune of Isale, Kanyosha in the areas of Muyira 
and Nyambuye in Bujumbura Province. Hundreds of people have 
fled the fighting between soldiers and armed groups. They came 
down from the hills to Bujumbura. Prime Minister Anatole 
Kanyenkiko today met all the people involved in maintaining 
security in rural Bujumbura and Bujumbura city. They studied 
the security situation in the province where peace has been 
seriously affected. [passage omitted] 

