<F P=100> SOUTHERN AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Zambia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government To Send 800 Soldiers to Rwanda </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government To Send 800 Soldiers to Rwanda </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB1206193994 Lusaka Zambia National Broadcasting Corporation 
Network in English 1800 GMT 12 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1206193994 </F>
<F P=104>  Lusaka Zambia National Broadcasting Corporation 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Zambia has mobilized 800 troops to help the United 
Nations in Rwanda, where more than 500,000 civilians have been 
slaughtered in a two-month civil war there. Defense Secretary 
Brigadier General Jack Mwaanga said in an interview with ZNBC 
[Zambia National Broadcasting Corporation] today that the 800 
soldiers are ready to leave for Rwanda any time. He said the 
contingent is on standby on the Copperbelt but cannot leave 
without special equipment which the Zambia Army has requested 
from other countries. Gen. Mwaanga said because of the 
difficult nature of the operation in Rwanda, the Zambian troops 
will need special equipment. 

</TEXT>

