<H3> <TI>   RPF Conducts Elections in Northern Prefecture </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    RPF Conducts Elections in Northern Prefecture </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA1406180394 (Clandestine) Radio Muhabura in English to 
Rwanda 1100 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1406180394 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Radio Muhabura </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Rwandan Patriotic Front [RPF] is conducting 
elections of local leaders in Prefecture Byumba. The exercise 
started on 12 June 1994 in Mukarange and Muranda sectors, in 
Prefecture Byumba. The elections were conducted democratically 
and (?peacefully). After the elections, the RPF officials 
explained the RPF political approach to Rwanda's problems. The 
delay in the implementation of the Arusha peace agreements and 
why the RPF has been forced to resume fighting were also 
explained to the gathering. The officials of the RPF repeated 
the call on the people who have fled their homes to return and 
settle down, for the RPF has re-established security for all 
persons in the areas under their control. The RPF chairman, 
Colonel Alexis Kanyarengwe, has said that even the Republican 
National Movement for Democracy and Development militias, who 
will lay down their arms and stop committing atrocities, will be 
free to go home and settle down. 

</TEXT>

