<H3> <TI>   ANC Rejects Allegations of Blackmailing Zulu King </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ANC Rejects Allegations of Blackmailing Zulu King </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB1306203594 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1600 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1306203594 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The ANC has rejected allegations that it wants to 
control the Zulu king. ANC spokesman Blade Nzimande said the 
organization was insisting that the king's status and 
remuneration be entrenched in the constitution. He accused the 
IFP [Inkatha Freedom Party] of blackmailing the king by paying 
