  [Text] In furtherance of the ongoing Liberian peace 
process, a delegation from the Transitional Legislative Assembly 
has arrived in Gbarnga. The latest move comes in the wake of 
recent pronouncements by the U.S. Government to cut off all aids 
and diplomatic efforts for peace in the Liberian crisis because 
of continuing setbacks in the full implementation of the peace 
accord. 
  The Transitional Legislative Assembly subcommittee on 
