<F P=100> CENTRAL AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Rwanda </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cease-Fire Broken; Intense Fighting Resumes in Kigali </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cease-Fire Broken; Intense Fighting Resumes in Kigali </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Hand-to-Hand Combat Reported </H4>

<F P=102> LD1706100894 Paris Radio France International in French 0900 
GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1706100894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio France International </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In Rwanda, very violent fighting broke out in the 
capital, Kigali, this morning. There were exchanges of 
artillery, mortar, and machine-gun fire between the government 
army and the RPF [Rwandan Patriotic Front] rebels. The UN 
soldiers on the spot were forced to suspend the evacuation of 
civilians trapped by the fighting. Talks on a cease-fire were 
expected to resume today. 
  In the capital, Kigali, eyewitnesses say that there is 
hand-to-hand fighting in the city centre. The RPF has in any 
case taken control of the Sainte Famille Church. Earlier, a 
shell hit the church, injuring 40 people. It was in this church 
that 60 adolescents took refuge and from which they were 
abducted [on Tuesday] and probably massacred by Hutu militiamen. 

</TEXT>

