<F P=101> Rwanda </F>
<H3> <TI>   RPF Admits Killing 1 UN Soldier </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    RPF Admits Killing 1 UN Soldier </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA1906170794 (Clandestine) Radio Muhabura in English to 
Rwanda 1115 GMT 19 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1906170794 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Radio Muhabura </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] One UN soldier was killed and another one wounded on 
Friday [17 June] when they were traveling near Shyorongi where 
fighting was taking place between Rwandan Patriotic Front [RPF] 
forces and government troops. 
  The RPF had earlier warned the UNAMIR not to use 
Kigali-Ruhengeri road without the consent of the RPF forces, but 
contrary to the warning the UN officers went through the roads. 
Their vehicle ended up landing in an ambush where fighting was 
taking place. The RPF soldiers fired at the vehicle and on 
coming closer found it was UN soldiers. 
  One officer, a major by rank, died instantly and one more 
was 
injured. The injured was given first aid and later taken to 
hospital. 

</TEXT>

